onaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Jzonn nods at Crydee as he takes a seat at the table.  &quot;It's been a while, hasn't it?  Our paths seems to meet for a time and then diverge again.  It appears this is another time of meeting.&quot;<br>
<br>
Turning to Casidy, Jzonn places a hand on her forearm and asks, &quot;What are our limitations, lass?&quot; <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/19/01 4:08:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> "We have two weeks, and meeting the Dain is just the first step... " a sense of foreboding overcomes Casidy, and her thoughts drift off momentarily, ice wastelands wet and dangerous appear in her mind.<br>
<br>
"Prohibitions?" speaking as if it were a foreign word in her mind "Oh yes, I am not to seek teleportation to the new world. I may recruit whatever other assistance is necessary, but I am to travel by boat and then traverse the land."<br>
<br>
Noticing the day well underway, Casidy looks around the table. "We should be getting underway as quickly as possible. I have had the innkeep prepare some provisions, more may be needed."<br>
<br>
At that moment, the barmaid tapped Casidy on the shoulder to get her attention and indicated that she was needed in the back room.<br>
<br>
"If you'll excuse me, they are requesting my presence in the back. The provisions are over in the corner, if you find materials lacking please let me know" Casidy pointed to a pile of warm weather gear and items stacked neatly on the table and floor of the corner table.<br>
<br>
Casidy rose and headed to the back of the bar to attend to some business matters with the innkeep.<br>
 <p><br><b><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2 COLOR="#6699cc">
---------------------------<br>
 Silent, Deadly         <br>
 Yeah, Right                  <br>
---------------------------<br>
<br>
~ Casidy Noteworthy</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uaedare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aedare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/19/01 10:14:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> As Casidy reached the back of the bar and got back to work, a young man whose armor bore the marks of the Freeport Militia stepped cautiously into the tavern.  &quot;I was told to give this message to the bard here?&quot; he whimpered, nervously, as though expecting to be attacked by something.  When gently reminded that a tavern often contained many bards, he dropped the note onto a table and fled.<br>
<br>
The note was extremely short and unsealed:<br>
<br>
&quot;Bard Casidy -<br>
<br>
In the course of our little discussion, I was reminded of certain things which I had left unfullfilled.  Although you may not have done anything directly to this end, your presence was useful to me.  Know that my hate does not fall upon you, and that my blade will be used in your defense if needed.  Do not let distances confuse you.  You will know how to call on me if the time comes.&quot;<br>
<br>
The note is signed &quot;Aedare Truedark&quot;, and, beneath, the seal of the Hall of Truth - inverted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrydeeossiriand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crydee Ossiriand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/20/01 12:31:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Crydee whispers low enough just for Casidy to hear, "You sure you want both of us on your trip. I don't think he likes me." Crydee points at Jzonn. "Perhaps I should ju..."<br>
<br>
Crydee notices the man wearing the Freeport Millitia insignia walk in and ducks under the table to hide. Even the lowest ranking of Millitia scum tended to attack him as if they had no though of self preservation. Crydee dreaded the though of spending more time than was absolutely necessary delivering inert potions.<br>
 <p><P><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="2">
<B>Crydee Ossiriand</B></FONT><BR>
<FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="1">
The Legndary Questing Ranger on Ayonae Ro<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.monsterweb.org" TARGET="_blank">http://monsterweb.org</A><BR>
<BR>
Person looking at my inventory... What quest loot do you drop?</FONT></P>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufebreeza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Febreeza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/21/01 8:16:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Grabs Crydee's arm and hauls him over to the supply stack.  <br>
<br>
&quot;No need to bother Casidy, she is obviously busy.  Let's get this pile sorted out so we can get going.  From the sounds of things, and what I have heard about this new land we could end up getting squeezed for time.&quot;<br>
<br>
Invites Jzonn and Qwik to come get some supplies as well.  &quot;Might as well share these among all of us, even if we have extra, I dare say we will have need of all of this before we are finished.&quot;<br>
<br>
Catches Casidy's eye and gives her a sly wink. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usirtaino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SirTainO</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/22/01 2:37:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jollyjokers.com/images/pally.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> "He must have seen me. <br>
There is no other possible reason why he suddenly started to walk faster; and now that he reached the Inn, didn't even look the Bard up before he dropped the letter.<br>
This Militia Messenger is not who he pretends to be. But who is he?"<br>
<br>
Taino tries to cover the flames of his sword which always reveal his personality at first sight. He should really have bought a sheath for it. The Commonlands are not as comfortable as they used to be. Since Sir Lucan D'Lere had to be stroke down for the good of the Temple of Truth, the Militia was on one hand been weakened, but on the other hand for sure willing to pay a good amount of money for his head. And Sergeant Slate seems never to sleep, dozens of times he had interrupted Taino's tries to weaken the Militias Infulence, at least in the Commons. <br>
<br>
Hidden behind a tree he peers through the Inns window and sees that must-be fake of a Militia Messenger losing his pokerface, starting to make mistakes.<br>
Never has he seen before a member of the Militia hiding in West Freeport. And the fact he came directly from the Temple of Truth just gives one explenation. The spy is not dead. Valeron was right, just as Gygus persumed, the spy that had to die was not the only one, maybe not even the right one. <br>
Thanks Erollisi, our fight will be successful.<br>
<br>
"Hail Sir"<br>
Taino was terrified for a second, turns around, wields his sword and shouts "For the Love of Erollisi and the Faith of the Kinghts of Truth, I protect the weaker ones and I will die with Honor!"<br>
<br>
Two shadows are looking at him, four eyes he feels on his face, body, sword. He will die but he will take them with him. He will not let them survive for the love of Erolli..<br>
<br>
"Nice sword there, you should think twice before you use it. Come in and have a drink..."<br>
<br>
Once again his eager almost cost him his life. He should finally stop doing everything alone and too fast. He will free the world, but not alone. Maybe. And for sure not today...<br>
Silent he follows the Ranger and the Warrioress in the Inn.<br>
Too ashamed to speak. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/22/01 3:10:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Jzonn moves over to the piles, taking an inventory.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Everything appears to be in order.  She seems to have accomodated most everything we'll need.  I'm sure we can pick up additional items from the Gnomes stationed in the Iceclad ocean base.  I'll just move the things I'll carry over here.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  He spends a few more minutes of review of the goods moving items around into a separate stack.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> We seem to be missing....</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Moving over to the innkeeper, a quick and quiet conversation ensues. Coin is exchanged into the innkeeper's hands and he moves off into the back store room.  &quot;We'll be a few minutes.  There are a few special provisions I didn't see here I wanted to have, just in case.&quot;<br>
<br>
After 20 minutes, the innkeeper returns and hands a bundle to Jzonn.  The bundle is placed in a pack set aside for him.  &quot;That does it for me.  Let me get cleaned up and into my travel clothes before we head out.&quot;  Shouldering a couple packs, Jzonn moves upstairs to collect the rest of his belongings.<br>
<br>
OOC: For those who do not know my style, the italicized text represents my thoughts. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/22/01 4:20:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> This inn was like a home of sorts for Casidy, and they felt the same about her. They had heard her making the preparations and they were sad to see her go. The innkeep had brought out a special cloak to protect her from the cold, a family heirloom.<br>
<br>
Casidy broke down into tears, the innkeeper and his wife had been so kind to her. Letting her play in their inn and basically letting her act as manager in the place. The barmaids were all crying over her leaving as well.<br>
<br>
"Chin up guys, I will be back" Casidy tried to say in her most reassuring voice. Even if internally she had reservations about her safety, there was no reason to worry these kind people. Casidy wiped away the tears, and passed out hugs all around.<br>
<br>
With a smile on her face, and wiping the tears from her face, she turned to walk back into the main part of the inn.<br>
<br>
"Well, friends... "Casidy surveyed the inn one last time as she spoke and fought to keep back further tears, "... if everything is in order, I think we should be underway."<br>
<br>
And with that she grabbed her packs, and headed out the door, drum in hand.<br>
<br>
Who would follow her, Casidy was unsure, but she needed to put a bit of distance between herself and this inn that was her former home. A bard should be like a gypsy, she thought and reassured herself, able to pick up and move at will.<br>
<br>
 <p><br><b><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2 COLOR="#6699cc">
---------------------------<br>
 Silent, Deadly         <br>
 Yeah, Right                  <br>
---------------------------<br>
<br>
~ Casidy Noteworthy</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufebreeza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Febreeza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/22/01 6:19:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Talks to the young Paladin after Jzonn heads upstairs, and explains where they are going and what has been planned so far.  As she invites him to join the group, she notices the young Bard lighting up for the door.<br>
<br>
She flicks her whip about the young Bard's waist and holds onto her there for a moment.  &quot;Would you gentlemen get the rest of the stuff together?  Casidy and I will start for the tunnel, you can catch up with us there.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hold up Casidy, me deary&quot; said Febreeza.  &quot;Let's make sure we are all in the same group before we go flying off shall we?&quot;<br>
<br>
She takes Casidy's arm and walks her outside and starts down the road knowing the men will catch up soon.  &quot;The men said they would meet us at the tunnel, if you need to talk I am here.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrydeeossiriand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crydee Ossiriand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/22/01 8:29:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Crydee looks over the supplies and provisions.<br>
"I don't need any of this. I am always prepared..."<br>
<br>
Crydee lets Febreeza inspect his own supplies for approval. One pack full of food, water, keys and one red rose. Another contained resistance gear and extra weapons. Two more contained nothing but summoned arrows. The last was normally empty, but contained Crydee's helmet at the moment.<br>
<br>
<br>
After Casidy and Febreeza leave, Crydee camoflages himself and follows them out.<br>
 <p><P><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="2"><B>Crydee Ossiriand</B><BR>
<FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="1">The Questing Ranger on Ayonae Ro<BR>
<A HREF="http://monsterweb.org">http://monsterweb.org</A><BR>
<BR>
Through your will has balance returned. Your deeds, your work for the good of all, will be remembered by anyone who walks beneath the canopy of a forest or roams the plains. Continue your vigil over nature's balance, Crydee.</FONT></P>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/23/01 8:07:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Jzonn completes his preparations upstairs.  He is washed and dressed.  All his belongings are neatly stored in packs.  One final check of the room and he heads down the stairs....to a nearly empty main room.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hmm.  It appears Casidy was really in a hurry to move along.  No matter.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Walking out of the main room into the morning sun, Jzonn begins to search the ground around the inn.  Several sets of footprints abound.  Going back and forth amongs a few sets, Jzonn kneels down and studies each in turn.  He finally comes to a set and notes the marks on the ground with great intensity.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> There she is...and Febreeza too.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Jzonn begins to cast a spell and the spirit of a wolf fills him with an increase of pace.  He follows the tracks before him onward, apparantly heading to the tunnel cut from the hill.  This strange passage leading to the norther desert of Ro is routinely used as a local market area.  As he approaches, he begins to hear the callings of the would be merchants.  He runs deeper into the tunnel, sensing Casidy is near.  He finally spots her and Febreeza standing at the ready.<br>
<br>
